ChainStreak respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your information is handled when you use the ChainStreak mobile application.

By using the app, you agree to the terms described in this Privacy Policy.

⸻

1. Information We Collect

ChainStreak does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data.

All habit data, notes, productivity scores, and usage information are stored locally on your device only.

We do not collect:
	•	Names
	•	Email addresses
	•	Phone numbers
	•	Location data
	•	Contacts
	•	Photos
	•	Usage analytics
	•	Advertising identifiers

⸻

2. How Your Data Is Used

Since all data is stored locally on your device:
	•	Your data is used only to operate the app’s features
	•	No data is sent to external servers
	•	No data is used for tracking, marketing, or analytics purposes

⸻

3. Data Sharing

ChainStreak does not share any data with:
	•	Third parties
	•	Advertising networks
	•	Analytics providers
	•	Cloud services
	•	Government authorities

Your data always remains on your device.

⸻

4. Data Storage and Security

All data is stored locally on your device using secure system storage methods provided by the operating system. You are fully responsible for backups, device security, and data recovery.

If you delete the app, all stored data will be permanently deleted.

⸻

5. Children’s Privacy

ChainStreak does not knowingly collect any data from children under the age of 13. Since no personal data is collected, the app is safe for general use.

⸻

6. Third-Party Services

ChainStreak does not use any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking services.

⸻

7. Your Rights

Because no personal data is collected or stored externally:
	•	There is no personal data to access, update, or delete from our servers
	•	All data management is fully controlled by you through your device

⸻

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be reflected within the app or on the official website where this policy is published.

⸻

9. Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact:

